author: Brendan Kurie bkurie@s-t.com
title: H.S. Roundup: Indians improve to 8-1 with sweep of Bridgewater-Raynham.
text: Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 9:19 PM By Brendan Kurie Posted Sep. 30, 2015 at 9:19 PM Â» Social News After dropping their first match last week, Dartmouth girls volleyball has wasted no time in igniting another winning streak. The Indians captured their second-straight victory on Wednesday evening, blanking Bridgewater-Raynham 3-0 at home. Game scores were 25-19, 25-19, 25-20. "We very consistent," coach Rachel Lassey said, "but we didn't play our best volleyball today." The Indians got 30 assists and 16 digs from Emma Caneira, who is nearing 1,000 career assists. Bailey Peach was equally impressive offensively and defensively, totaling 15 kills and 14 digs. Lexie Viveiros added 12 digs, Skylar Barthelmes slammed seven kills and Victoria LaBree had five kills. The Indians (8-1, 1-1 OCL) host Durfee on Friday for their Dig Pink match, which raised over $1,000 for breast cancer awareness last year. Fans are invited to buy from a bake sale and take part in a 50-50 raffle. GNB Voc-Tech 3, Dighton-Rehoboth 1 Riley Thomas kept the offense rolling with 25 assists as the Bears won 25-11, 25-13, 24-26, 25-20. ... "We used this opportunity to play with the rotation a little bit and try some changes," coach Erika Vassal said. "We got a little carried away in Set 3 with some unforced errors, but reined it back in in Set 4." ... Victoria Gregoire had 23 digs and two service aces, while Alexis Teves added 12 kills, five digs and was 13-for-13 serving. ... The Bears (5-4, 4-3 SCC) play at Wareham on Friday. Blue Hills 3, Westport 2 The Wildcats were up 2-1, but a young team couldn't quite close out the Warriors. Game scores were 23-25, 25-23, 20-25, 25-14, 15-10. ... "Overall, we played well," coach Mike King said. "They kind of got into our heads when we got down in the fourth game and we didn't recover." ... Hailey Charest led the attack with 11 kills, while Cierra Yim added eight aces and 12 assists. ... The Wildcats (3-7, 1-3 Mayflower Small) play at Sacred Heart on Tuesday. Fairhaven 3, Bourne 2 After dropping a close fifth set to Case earlier this week, the Blue Devils needed to prove they could win the close one. Game scores were 18-25, 25-22, 25-16, 26-28, 26-14. ... "Another close one," coach Karen Arsenault said. "At least we came out on top this time. I think certain people really stepped up the last few plays." ... One of those was Kacey McKenna, who finished with a career-high 18 kills in what Arsenault called "probably the best night of her career." ... Sierra Canastra anchored the Blue Devils' block, adding seven kills. "She was amazing at the net," Arsenault said. "She had a touch on almost every hard-hit ball." ... Hayleigh Aubut came up with 30 digs, three kills and one ace; Stormie Becotte dished out 45 assists; Amanda Jones was strong at the service line and added 11 digs. ... Fairhaven (9-1, 7-1 SCC) hosts New Bedford on Friday. BOYS CROSS COUNTRY Bridgewater-Raynham 28, Dartmouth 28 The Indians lost the sixth-runner tiebreaker to suffer their first loss of the season. ... Greg Martin was second in 17:09, Advika Rajapaske was third in 17:19, Bryce Boswell was fourth in 17:34, Seth Chaves was eighth in 18:21 and Ben Rioux was 10th in 18:58. ... Dartmouth is 2-1, including a 1-1 mark in the Old Colony League. GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY Bridgewater-Raynham 26, Dartmouth 33 Despite three top-five finishes, the Indians fell to 1-2 overall, 0-2 in the Old Colony League. ... Dartmouth was led by Caitlyn Demers (2nd, 20:02), Maddie Lynch (3rd, 20:06), Rachel Gin (5th, 21:25), Phoebe Cousens (11th, 24:49) and Pat Magpayo (12th, 26:56). By Brendan Kurie
